si_remarks: The study site is dominated by three eucalypt species representing a range of bark types: Eucalyptus obliqua L’Hér (deep fibrous ‘stringybark’), E. radiata Sieber ex DC (short fibrous ‘peppermint’ bark), and E. rubida H. Deane and Maiden (smooth ‘gum’ bark). The understorey is sparse and patchy, mainly consisting of native perennial grasses and Austral bracken (Pteridium esculentum (G.Forst.) Cockayne).
